See https://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.monitoring.html
See https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/111997
See https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/116413

I'll stick with the current names, they look at least somewhat consistent.

I previously had something different, which didn't work well:
https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6144/commits/e49c5b8aef9933c28a1b29003dae5f6e5bb68a5b

It's a bit more subtle: we usually need *some* node where we had pass statements (there are probably cases where a simple `None` would bother us), but I wanted to avoid nested empty `StatListNodes` to avoid bloating the overall tree structure. Thus the "put in an empty `StatListNode` but not inside another `StatListNode`" because we definitely don't need it there.

I now took the opportunity to generalise this so that we flatten all `StatListNodes`, rather than just discarding nested empty ones. Let's see if that works.
